description:
As an engineer in the tech industry, I don't come across many opportunities to dress formally. So when my friend told me one day that she lucked out with a reservation at Kokkari Estiatorio, I leaped at the occasion to flaunt my favorite blazer and loafers. As the great Barney Stinson once said, "Suit up!"

Kokkari serves what is hands-down the best Greek food in all of the Bay. Their dinner menu predominantly consists of meats that are seasoned just enough to enhance the flavors, but never to overpower. Everything about this dining experience is on-point: the rustic and romantic vibe, the accommodating service, and of course the delicious meal.

Their only slip up of the evening was giving my friend somebody else's box of leftovers to take home. This might have pissed some people off, but thankfully she's a good sport. In fact, she was more than happy to try some of the half-eaten moussaka the following morning!

MEZETHES
// Kolokithokeftethes ($11.75) - 4 stars
I really enjoyed the crispiness of the zucchini cakes and the mintiness of the yogurt dressing.

// Octapodaki tou Yiorgou ($17) - 5 stars
My friend doesn't usually eat octopus, but had to make an exception for this dish. It was tender and chewy without a single trace of sliminess.

KIRIOS PIATO
// Psari Psito: Branzino ($45.50) - 5 stars
The sea bass looked so simple yet it tasted amazing. I keep telling myself that I need to learn how to cook fish like this. It'll be a useful skill to keep myself sane during my next weight loss challenge.

// Arnisia Paidakia ($45.95) - 5 stars
Lightly dressed in lemon-oregano vinaigrette and cooked perfectly medium-rare, these three lamb chops were jam-packed with meaty flavor. They also didn't have much of a lingering gamy aftertaste. The Kokkari potatoes that came on the side were also bomb, with their crispy exterior and fluffy insides.

GLYKA
// Pagoto Baklava ($9.75) - 4 stars
I could totally see Baklava lovers go crazy for this unique ice cream flavor. As for me, I thought that the syrup was a tad too sweet and the pastry shreds a tad too flaky.

Couldn't be better;
Seaside in Santorini; 
Top tier food indeed.
